        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 4.  TERMINATION OF MARRIAGE
Art. 101.  Termination of marriage
Marriage terminates upon:
The death of either spouse.
Divorce.
A judicial declaration of its nullity, when the marriage is relatively null.
The issuance of a court order authorizing the spouse of a person presumed dead to remarry, as provided by law.</p>
        </content>
